.TH ipk-client 1
.SH NAME ipk-client - client for solving mathematical
operations
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ipk-client
.IP ip
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ipk-client
client for solving mathematical operations, connects to
server, asks for math operations and sends back results
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \ip
Set the IP Address of the server that should be used for communication for receiving mathetmatical operations. IP Address can be a IPv4, or IPv6
.SH BUGS
There are no bugs on me! (of course there are..)
At the moment, server can't be resolved by hostname (probably in newer release)
No other operations than +,-,*,/ are working but the system is ready to be upgraded to solve other operations for example modulo, etc.
